Regional Registry Portal latest news

February 2018

Regional Registry Portal presented at the third EBRD Western Balkans Summit

London, 26th of February 2018. Mr. Zvonko Obradovic, Director of the Serbian Business Registry Agency presented at the third EBRD Western Balkans Summit in London the RRP services, covering live data from Serbian and Macedonian companies and persons and test data from Slovenian, Albanian and Bosnian (Republic of Srpska and Federation of BiH jurisdictions) registries

December 2017

First regional project workshop held in Belgrade

Belgrade, 14-15 December 2017. Serbian Business Registry Agency hosted a workshop with EBRD and the Central Register of Republic of Macedonia, discussing the RRP platform, its technical requirements and possibilities for other countries to join in. Slovenia, Albania, Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Romania agreed to share sample data for companies and persons for demonstration of the portal at the London’s EBRD WB6 summit in February 2018.

November 2017

New services to support ALM and beneficial ownership requirements

Belgrade / Skopje, November 2017. In agreement with Serbian Business Registry Agency and the Central Register of Republic of Macedonia, REAKTIV designed a set of services to allow tracing of full list of connected entities to support ALM prevention and beneficial ownership tracking between the two countries.

September 2017

Regional Registry Portal project kick-off

Belgrade, September 2017. Serbian Business Registry Agency with the financial support of EBRD contracted REAKTIV ( www.reaktiv.com.mk) to design, develop and implement the services and platform for the Regional Registry Portal. The project should go live with its services in mid-2018.

About

 

Regional Registry Portal is a joint service delivery platform of the official registry institutions in Southeast Europe.

The portal is the first data service provider in Southeast Europe offering extensive business intelligence by combining financial and statutory information from directly connected registry sources. We offer services created from data obtained with direct connection to the official registries in the region, without any intermediaries.

This allows us to lead the data analytics market in Southeast Europe, providing most accurate information, combining largest scope of data and offering deepest industry insights, comparable between multiple countries.

All the services are created with unified methodology, allowing cross-border comparability of data, respecting multilingual and multicurrency conversions. The basic searches of all legal entities and persons are free, so you are able to find the right entity to look for detailed services.

Please take a look what data and services we offer to understand their specific legal and financial semantics.

Currently the portal is connected to the official registries in Serbia and Macedonia, but several other countries in the region are joining soon.

Please take a look which countries and registries are providing data to the portal.

Regional Registry Portal is a result of the project funded by the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development ( www.ebrd.com), in its efforts to help establish successful instruments in a Single Market in the Western Balkans region.

The project started in September 2017 as a joint collaboration between the Serbian Business Registry Agency ( www.apr.gov.rs) and the Macedonian Central Registry ( www.crm.com.mk) and will go live with the full scope of commercial services between the two countries in the second half of 2018.

General Help Page

Learn how to make basic search and order related services

01 Main Header

Your basic search starts on the "Home Page" in the main header

02 Login/Register

If you are not registered, use the header's top right buttons to register, or log in to our system if you are.

03 Search Company or Person

After you log in, select "Company" or "Person" on the radio buttons to make the search.

04 Select country

Select all countries in the region or specific country you are interested in.

05 Select subject of interest

Select the result you are interested in and go to the next page.

06 Show services

This page shows more information about the company or person you selected, with all the services connected to that particular entity.

Please select service from the list of services.

07 Service information

When you select a service, we provide service information with sample data, price and option to purchase the service.

08 Purchase service

You have the option to temporarily put this item to the shopping cart for later, or immediately make the purchase.

You can purchase special packages, subscriptions, and discounts in the "Subscriptions" section.

Additionally, you can access the "My Subscriptions" section and under the "Corporate Subscriptions " tab, check if you have existing corporate subscriptions you can use.

09 Proceed to check out.

Finish the purchase by completing the transaction.

10 View your purchased report.

After purchasing the report, you get a notification in the header. You can access the report by clicking in the notification area or by accessing "Reports" from the left-side menu.
